                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-1281" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-1281" type="surname" value="ROBERTS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-1281" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN ROBERTS</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in High-street, Deptford, and deal in earthen<lb></lb>ware. On the 28th of March, I heard a noise in my shop—I went into the shop and saw the prisoner—he asked me if a gentleman at Blackheath, named Foster, had ordered some decanters—I said, "No"—he said, a gentleman of that name was coming, and he just called to put me on my guard—he then went away, and I missed these cruets from a stand on the chair—I followed, and took him with them in his pocket.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner pleaded poverty.)</p>
